-- Arsenal Offers Thierry Henry Loan Deal, Daily Mail Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2011-12-29T09:37:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/arsenal-offers-thierry-henry-loan-deal-daily-mail-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Henry Return  Arsenal has offered former striker  Thierry Henry  a two-
month loan deal that may see him play in seven Premier League
games, the  Daily Mail  reported.  The Gunners’ all-time top scorer doesn’t have to return to
his current team, the New York Red Bulls, until March, the Mail
said.  Chelsea Signing  Chelsea is negotiating personal terms with  Gary Cahill 
after agreeing to a 7 million ($10.8 million) fee for the Bolton
defender, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The Blues are talking to Cahill’s agent with a view to
signing him next month, the Mirror said.  Malouda Switch  Chelsea’s Florent Malouda could join former Blues coach
 Carlo Ancelotti  at Paris Saint-Germain in the January transfer
window,  the Sun  reported.  Malouda, 31, says he is not getting enough playing time at
Stamford Bridge, according to the Sun. Media reports in  France 
say PSG is close to hiring Ancelotti as coach.  Tottenham Striker  Tottenham striker Roman Pavlyuchenko will consider an offer
from Anzhi Makhachkala after not starting a Premier League game
this season, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  He had previously ignored overtures from the remote Russian
team that signed Samuel Eto’o in September, the Mirror said,
citing his agent Oleg Artemov.  To contact the reporters on this story:
